title: Introducing DEZI SKIN
description:
Introducing DEZI SKIN
CLARO QUE C - VITAMIN C GLOW SERUM 
$64

Launching Exclusively on http://deziskin.com 
April 8th 2021 9 AM PST

Bright, glowy, and even skin? CLARO QUE C (of course) ! This innovative formula is made with 15% PURE VITAMIN C.

TELL ME MORE:
Potent forms of vitamin C are infused into the water and oil phases of this serum, allowing skin absorption on two levels: the water-loving and oil-loving parts of the skin. As an antioxidant, vitamin C helps fight the effects of free radicals and reduce the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles. It also helps reduce the appearance of dark spots and uneven skin tone to give the skin a more youthful glow. 

Fragrance free
Paraben free
Triclosan free
Cruelty free
Gluten free
Vegan

USAGE: 
Unlike some vitamin C products, this formula boasts a non-sticky texture that makes it easy and enjoyable to use. Apply 1-2 pumps to clean, dry face. Use morning before sunscreen or evening after cleansing. Shake well before use. For External Use only. Use as Directed. Avoid contact with eyes. If irritation continues, contact a doctor and discontinue use.

WHAT‚ÄôS INSIDE: 
Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate (THD):  An active form of oil-soluble Vitamin C which improves collagen synthesis and significantly brightens & evens skin tone.

High-purity Ethyl Ascorbic Acid: Over 99% purity Ethyl Ascorbic Acid that is proven to brighten and tone sun-damaged skin including dark spots. Additionally, it provides powerful anti-aging and antioxidant effects.

DP-C:  Ascorbic Acid & Glutathione conjugated to gold submicroparticles synergistically work together to dramatically enhance skin penetration.

Green Plum:  Energizes dull looking skin, induces skin brightening, reduces the appearance of skin redness and improves overall skin tone evenness. Stimulates the expression of SVCT-I, the vitamin C ‚Äútransporter‚Äù of the skin. 

DEZI Youth Juice:  An all-natural, custom blend of Mexican Plum fruit, Dragon Fruit, Acai Berry, Tamarind, Mango, Soursop, Guava, and Avocado extracts, rich in antioxidants.

*All ingredients above are at active levels in the formula*

INGREDIENTS:
Water, Ethyl Ascorbic Acid, Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, Propanediol, Coconut Alkanes, Polyester-4, Dimethicone, Glycerin, Ethylhexyl Olivate, Glyceryl Caprylate, Ascorbic Acid, Glutathione, Gold, Sodium Acrylates Copolymer, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Polyglyceryl-4 Oleate, Ammonium Acryloyldimethyltaurate/VP Copolymer, Butylene Glycol, Polysilicone-11, Citric Acid, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter, Caprylhydroxamic Acid, Sorbitol, Terminalia Ferdinandiana Fruit Extract, Alteromonas Ferment Extract, Annona Muricata Fruit Extract, Euterpe Oleracea Fruit Extract, Hylocereus Undatus Fruit Extract, Mangifera Indica (Mango) Fruit Extract, Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Fruit Extract, Prunus Domestica Fruit Extract, Psidium Guajava Fruit Extract, Tamarindus Indica Extract, Caprylyl Glycol, Decyl Glucoside, 1,2-Hexanediol, Xanthan Gum, Hexylene Glycol, Phenoxyethanol.

Net wt 30 ML / 1 FL OZ
MADE IN USA

title: TRYING OUT THE NEW DOSE OF COLORS FOUNDATION FEAT. KATY
description:
Like and Subscribe ‚û°Ô∏è http://bit.ly/desiperkins

FINAL THOUGHTS ON THE FOUNDATION: Overall I love this foundation. I will say it does oxidize, so it did get darker after application, which is fine because I felt like I needed a darker color in the olive undertone anyway. It felt very light weight on the skin‚Äîit didn‚Äôt feel like I was wearing makeup, which everyone loves lol. I don‚Äôt think it was that matte, so you definitely need a powder, but once it was set it, it definitely all set. It also had a natural radiant finish, which you guys know I love. Anyway, congratulations Anna and Dose of Colors for this launch!! It‚Äôs been in the works for so long and I‚Äôm glad it‚Äôs finally out for everyone to play with!

Save the Children believes every child deserves a future. In the United States and around the world, we work every day to give children a healthy start in life, the opportunity to learn and protection from harm. When crisis strikes, and children are most vulnerable, we are always among the first to respond and the last to leave. We ensure children's unique needs are met and their voices are heard. We deliver lasting results for millions of children, including those hardest to reach. title: Sugar Skull Halloween Tutorial
description:
Hi beauties! So excited to share this tutorial with you! Sugar skulls come in all different forms and I wanted to bring to life a more realistic skull with the embellishments of a traditional sugar skull. I know this doesn't have as much color as a lot of traditional sugar skulls do, but I wanted to do something a little different. I wanted it to remain beautiful and real while still letting your own face shine through. 

I created the head piece with an old Halloween top hat that I already had. I used fake flowers from a craft store and just hot glue gunned them on. The little skull is from the 99cent store and the pearls are also from the flower section at the craft store. Try and use what you have or go pick up some inexpensive items to create something that looks expensive. Halloween is a time to use creativity and just have fun with things. Hope you all enjoyed. 

Trick or treat
